e?gid=charmroxors>Charmroxors</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#330000>(3/4/03 1:13:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=157.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How Viable is Charm soloing before lvl 50+</span><hr size=1> thats all i did in the lower teens all the way up until present day, charm solo'ing is always best... even if the spells and such arent the most reliable at the early levels, it prepares / makes you better for when you've reached the high end game where charm solo'ing is excellent. i'd say its probably quicker than a &quot;good xp group&quot; but its a lot more hectic, you've got a lot more to worry about while charming.<br>
<br>
lvls 12-18 or so ... i charmed spiders in oasis<br>
lvls 18-25, i'd charm in paladul until i got into a group<br>
lvls 25-35, zelniaks &amp; mushrooms in DSP<br>
lvls 35-40, walruses in EW (near Kael)<br>
lvls 40-48, frost giant scouts in GD (near EW zoneline)<br>
lvls 48-53, ravishing drolvargs in DL... awesome pet<br>
53+ wolves in PoN and puslings in PoD (duoing with a wiz)<br>
<br>
hope it helps even if just a little bit. <br>
 <p><img border=0 src="http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/Charmroxors/fullsize/barcodesig.jpg" /><br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=555166" target="_new">inspect me</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mirnim@eqenchantersrealm>Mirnim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#330000>(3/10/03 5:21:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=157.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> How Viable is Charm soloing before lvl 50+</span><hr size=1> Very viable.<br>
<br>
I played my enchanter mostly solo from 25 to 50. At lower levels, below 34, I mostly fear kited. Then I switched to charm solo and I loved it.<br>
<br>
True, it is a drag until you get the hang of it, but once you know what to do, Exp just flies by. One constrain, SOW is a must unless you hunt some very special (slow) mobs. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=foslchan>foslchan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#330000>(3/31/03 12:41:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=157.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How Viable is Charm soloing before lvl 50+</span><hr size=1> I would suggest to have a partner that can snare the mob, once snare, it is so easy to control your charmed pet.  Always to have sow on too.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sinnjatorix>Sinnjatorix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#330000>(4/14/03 6:10:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=157.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://w1.853.telia.com/~u85304784/pics/eq/Stringius.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How Viable is Charm soloing before lvl 50+</span><hr size=1> How usefull is fearkiting for a chanter? considerig the lack of snare that is. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=206618">Dark elf wizard</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->,<br>
