<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=64829">Barbarian rogue</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=astyd>astyd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#330000>(4/14/03 8:15:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=157.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Fearkiting</span><hr size=1> <br>
Fearkiting is not really an option.  I used Fear as a last resort crowd control spell when we needed to escape.  Chances of bringing back adds is just too high.<br>
<br>
