ed heals since they have tons of hp and it's easier to grab a new one than to heal them anyway.<br>
<br>
With one of those pets you can clear the entire rockhopper cave, the rock monsters and some wolfs before respawn.  I don't know of another zone with such overpowered pets. <p><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=177765">Lich Drainer the Heretic</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Arch Lich not on Luclin anymore<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=254868">Baron Dezkert -- Assassin</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
Meren's only friend <!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=felicelilithniessa>Felice Lilith Niessa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#330000>(4/22/03 8:07:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=157.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Griffawn Charming in NK and EK</span><hr size=1> Picking a leaf from my druid days I went back with my enchanter and did 16 - 19 in NK and EK taking advantage of the infamous undercon Griffawns, which will munch quite happily through most mobs, only taking significant damage against crag spiders and gorge hounds.<br>
<br>
I had a KEI and 10 dose SoW potion, and the xp pretty much flew by. Should be possible without KEI, but there would be downtime. However the SoW is mandatory.<br>
<br>
Setup:<br>
<br>
Mes (24 sec version)<br>
Tash<br>
Charm<br>
Haste (repeat as mana permits)<br>
<br>
Kill:<br>
<br>
Mes (optional)<br>
Tash (optional)<br>
Root (optional - but recommended on the fast mobs)<br>
Slow<br>
Nuke (as mana permits)<br>
<br>
Charm will of course occassionally break at the worst possible moment, so you have to have SoW. A druid partner could be extremely effective, especially if you object to doing the KEI thing at low level. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showPrevMessage?topicID=157.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showNextMessage?topicID=157.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=157.topic&index=8><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/traditional/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.threadControl?topicID=157.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/traditional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=157.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=157.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub136.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="eqenchantersrealmfrm11">General<option value="eqenchantersrealmadminnotices">Admin Notices<option value="eqenchantersrealmfrm12">Equipment<option value="eqenchantersrealmspells">Spells<option value="eqenchantersrealmfaqs">FAQs<option value="eqenchante